# data-models

Key data model relationships between Meetings and Documents:

## Meeting Data Model
Importance Score: 90

Core Structure:
- Sophisticated meeting bundle model that combines:
  - Raw meeting transcripts
  - Extracted signals (Decisions, Action Items, Blockers, Risks, Ideas)
  - Signal status workflow states (approved, rejected, archived)
  - Accountability tracking integration
  - Multi-source transcript merging (Pocket, Teams)

## Document Data Model  
Importance Score: 85

Core Structure:
- Signal extraction and categorization
- Contextual relationship mappings to meetings
- Domain-aware conversational system links
- Sprint-aware context associations

## Relationship Management
Importance Score: 85

- Unified meeting data ingestion system links to document artifacts
- Automated summary generation connects meetings to documents
- Signal extraction pipeline maintains cross-references

